The man was shot in his chest but was able to get into his car and drive away. However he could not get to safety and died near the Durban Magistrate's Court in Somtseu Road. Rescue Care paramedic Garrith Jamieson said that on arrival they "found that a vehicle had collided through the fence of the Durban Magistrates Court. On assessing the scene they found that a male in his forties had sustained injuries including that of a gunshot to his upper body"."There was nothing more Paramedics could do for the man and he was declared deceased on the scene." Police were attending to the scene. - TMG Digtial/The Times